Creating a bucket is an **admin/server-side** operation in Appwrite, so you should **not** do that directly in browser code. The normal pattern is:

1. **Create the bucket once** on your server or in an Appwrite Function.
2. Use the **Appwrite Web SDK** in the browser to upload the image and generate a preview URL.

## 1) Create the bucket once (server-side)

```ts
// create-bucket.ts
import { Client, Storage, Permission, Role } from 'node-appwrite';

const client = new Client()
  .setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
  .setProject(process.env.APPWRITE_PROJECT_ID!)
  .setKey(process.env.APPWRITE_API_KEY!);

const storage = new Storage(client);

await storage.createBucket({
  bucketId: 'images',
  name: 'Images',
  permissions: [
    Permission.create(Role.users()), // signed-in users can upload files
    Permission.read(Role.users()),   // signed-in users can read bucket metadata/list if needed
  ],
  fileSecurity: true, // required if you want per-file permissions
  maximumFileSize: 10 * 1024 * 1024, // 10 MB
  allowedFileExtensions: ['jpg', 'jpeg', 'png', 'webp'],
});
```

If the bucket already exists, skip this step.

---

## 2) Upload a file and get a preview URL with the Web SDK

```html
<input id="image-input" type="file" accept="image/*" />
<button id="upload-btn">Upload</button>
<img id="preview" alt="Uploaded image preview" />
```

```ts
// web.ts
import { Client, Account, Storage, ID, Permission, Role } from 'appwrite';

const client = new Client()
  .setEndpoint('https://<REGION>.cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
  .setProject('<PROJECT_ID>');

const account = new Account(client);
const storage = new Storage(client);

const bucketId = 'images';

async function uploadImageAndGetPreview(input: HTMLInputElement) {
  const file = input.files?.[0];
  if (!file) throw new Error('Please select an image file.');
  if (!file.type.startsWith('image/')) {
    throw new Error('Selected file must be an image.');
  }

  const me = await account.get();

  const uploaded = await storage.createFile({
    bucketId,
    fileId: ID.unique(),
    file,
    permissions: [
      Permission.read(Role.any()),          // public preview/view
      Permission.update(Role.user(me.$id)), // only owner can update
      Permission.delete(Role.user(me.$id)), // only owner can delete
    ],
  });

  const previewUrl = storage.getFilePreview({
    bucketId,
    fileId: uploaded.$id,
    width: 800,
    height: 800,
    quality: 80,
  });

  return {
    file: uploaded,
    previewUrl: previewUrl.toString(),
  };
}

const input = document.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>('#image-input')!;
const button = document.querySelector<HTMLButtonElement>('#upload-btn')!;
const preview = document.querySelector<HTMLImageElement>('#preview')!;

button.addEventListener('click', async () => {
  const { previewUrl } = await uploadImageAndGetPreview(input);
  preview.src = previewUrl;
});
```

## Permission notes

- `fileSecurity: true` on the bucket is what makes the per-file `permissions` in `createFile()` take effect.
- `Permission.read(Role.any())` makes the image preview URL public.
- If you want the file to stay private, replace that with:

```ts
Permission.read(Role.user(me.$id))
```

